    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that. but even if critics say it's ideological, it's still taught in basically every law school as a legitimate, major theory, right? is there any actual scholarly support for the idea that it's just a \"philosophical constraint\" or a ruse, or is that more of a political talking point?",
